EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the allowable maximum heat loss through building walls.
EventItemMatterName: Allowable maximum heat loss through building walls.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the permitting and monitoring of portable generators.
EventItemMatterName: Permitting and monitoring of portable generators.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the noise standard for commercial establishments.
EventItemMatterName: Noise standard for commercial establishments.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the administration for children's services to provide an annual report regarding high school graduation rates of youth in foster care.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the administration for children's services to provide information regarding high school graduation rates of youth in foster care.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Youth Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of youth and community development to review strategies and create a plan of action to protect children who qualify for special immigrant juvenile status.
EventItemMatterName: Review strategies and create a plan of action to protect children who qualify for special immigrant juvenile status.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of sanitation to collect and report data related to the unlawful posting of printed material.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the dept of sanitation to collect and report data related to the unlawful posting of printed material.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Aging
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to providing assistance to seniors with bed bugs in their homes.
EventItemMatterName: Providing assistance to seniors with bed bugs in their homes.

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign legislation which designates as professional misconduct, engaging in sexual orientation change efforts by mental health care professionals upon patients under 18 years of age.
EventItemMatterName: Designates as professional misconduct, engaging in sexual orientation change efforts by mental health care professionals upon patients under 18 years of age.

EventItemMatterName: Michael Sandy Act

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on Capital One to amend their individual credit card agreements regarding how and when they contact cardholders for debt collection.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city New York, in relation to requiring the department of environmental protection to notify water customers who are owners of tax class two properties, by mail, of large charges that could indicate a potential leak.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the dept of environmental protection to notify water customers who are owners of tax class 2 properties, by mail, of large charges that could indicate a potential leak.

EventItemTitle: Resolution concerning an amendment to the District Plan of the Kings Highway Business Improvement District that authorizes additional services and modifies existing services for the district, and setting the date, time and place for the public hearing of the local law authorizing additional services and modifying existing services for the district.

EventItemMatterName: Amending the obligations of owners to provide notice to their tenants for service interruptions.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign S.6570/A.8742, requiring all textbooks to also refer to the Sea of Japan as the East Sea.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring all textbooks to also refer to the Sea of Japan as the East Sea. (S.6570/A.8742)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of A.8587/S.6386, which would amend the New York State Penal Law by increasing the penalties for drivers who cause serious physical injury or death to another person while knowingly operating a motor vehicle without a license or with a revoked or suspended license.
EventItemMatterName: Increasing the penalties for drivers who cause serious physical injury or death to another person while knowingly operating a motor vehicle without a license or with a revoked or suspended license. (A.8587/S.6386)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring all children with an individualized education program to be transported in buses with air-conditioning.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring all children with an individualized education program to be transported in buses with air-conditioning.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York in relation to an invasive species advisory board.
EventItemMatterName: An invasive species advisory board.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Parks and Recreation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to renaming two thoroughfares and public places in the Borough of Queens, Court Square East and Court Square West, and to amend the official map of the city of New York accordingly.
EventItemMatterName: Renaming two thoroughfares and public places, Queens, Court Square East and Court Square West.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation

EventItemMatterName: Requiring signage as to the location of libraries.

EventItemMatterName: MTA to install soundproofing systems near schools where subway and train noise reach disruptive decibel levels.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York City Department of Education to require that all public school students receive age-differentiated anti-bullying instruction and complete an anti-bullying course focused especially on cyberbullying.
EventItemMatterName: Require that all public school students receive age-differentiated anti-bullying instruction and complete an anti-bullying course focused especially on cyberbullying.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation

EventItemMatterName: The right of way of pedestrians and bicyclists.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter and the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the provision of vacation leave and employment.
EventItemMatterName: Provision of vacation leave and employment.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection

EventItemMatterName: Filing semiannual reports on catch basin cleanup and maintenance

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to borough-specific coordination of snow event response and communication.
EventItemMatterName: Borough-specific coordination of snow event response and communication.

EventItemMatterName: Establish a public campaign financing system for campaigns for the office of NYS Comptroller.
